column2: Sunshine but hazy.  Wind is 0-5 mph.
Sunny but hazy- wind at 15 mph.  Had three days of high winds and whitecaps at times.
Sunny- calm- and just a bit of algae.
Blustery.  Algae blooms very evident but limited to phytoplankton.
Northwest wind at 5 mph- and algae blooms are receding.
Little to no algae blooms- sunny and calm.
Sunny and calm.  No algae blooms.
The temperature is 77 degrees- sunny- calm- and no algae.
The temperature is 75 degrees- sunny- calm- and no algae bloom.
The temperature is 77 degrees- brisk wind- and no algae bloom.
The temperature is 73 degrees- hazy- calm- and no algae bloom.
Clear- calm- and the temperature is 80 degrees.
Clear- sunny- 80 degrees- ripple on the lake- and no bloom.
Clear- breezy- the temperature is 78 degrees- and phytoplankton starting to appear.
70 degrees- clear- calm- and radio larian phytoplankton floating.
Sunny and calm.  Phytoplankton is decreasing.
Calm and sunny- 56 degrees- and no algae.
Sunny- light breeze- and no algae.
The water is greenish brown.  Detritus and phytoplankton are increasing turbidity since last reading.  Sunny.
The temperature is 28 degrees- sunny- light breeze.  Saw 70-80 mallards and one loon.  Last reading for 1988.
The temperature is 78 degrees- hazy sunlight- windy- and much boat activity.  Sorry we are late in getting started this year. Water level: up 6" from last year
Sunny- clear- calm- 75 degrees- and little algae.
Sunny- clear- calm- 70 degrees- and some algae.
Sunny- clear- calm- 72 degrees- and some algae.
65 degrees- sunny- and calm.  Amazed at the clarity.  Water level: Up 2" from last report
65 degrees- clear- slight breeze and small amount of algae.
The temperature is 65 degrees- windy- sunny- and minimal boat traffic.
The temperature is 50 degrees.  Clear- sunny day.  Light winds following a week with high winds.
The temperature is 52 degrees- clear- sunny- brisk wind- and some algae.  Beautiful color on the trees.
Intended to get another reading but winter came too early.  Water temperature is 39 degrees.  Loons and mallards are still here.  See you in the spring!
Does not seem as clear as normal.  Visibility less than normal scuba diving 5/31.
Had a rainstorm last night.  Lots of boat activity today.  Looks like pollen in water.
Public perception due to phytoplankton levels.
Partly cloudy day. hardly any boat traffic.
No other boats on lake- cloudy day.
It was a sunny day about 80 degrees. It was a sunny day about 80 degrees. Assume noon
We went out in our canoe.  The weather was mostly cloudy and about 75 degrees.
The weather was in the 60's and it was a sunny day.  I saw two eagles and one loon.
It was a sunny day.  I saw a bald eagle flying over the lake.
It was a sunny day and the temperature was about 75 degrees. We saw a loon and a baby loon.
